{"questionId":"3495762","questionHtml":"<p>By solving the differential equation, show that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>+</mo><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mo>(</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></mfrac></msqrt></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>∫</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>d</mi><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">y</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>∫</mo><mfrac><mi>x</mi><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo> </mo><mi>d</mi><mo> </mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">x</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mo>(</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>substituting <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>y</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>y</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mo>(</mo><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>)</mo></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn>